Northern Ireland Beats Faroes to Go Third in Euro 2012 Qualifying Group

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-08-10T23:13:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/northern-ireland-beats-faroes-to-go-third-in-euro-2012-qualifying-group.html
Pat McCourt scored twice as  Northern
Ireland  beat the Faroe Islands 4-0 in a qualifying match for
soccerâ€™s 2012 European Championship.  McCourt got goals in the 71st and 88th minutes last night
after Aaron Hughes and Steven Davis had put the home team 2-0 up
at Windsor Park in Belfast.  The victory moves Northern Ireland into third place in
Group C, two points behind second-place Slovenia, which has
played one game more, and seven back of leader Italy.  The winners of the nine qualifying groups, along with the
second-place team with the most points, qualify for Euro 2012
with co-hosts Poland and Ukraine. The remaining eight second-
place teams will play off for the final four spots.  The next round of qualifying matches will be played Sept.
2. The 2012 European Championships will be played June 8 to July
1 in Ukraine and  Poland .  To contact the reporter on this story:
